XRD was characterized to analyze the structure of samples (Fig. 1
                        ). The XRD pattern of C-dots shows a wide peak at ∼23°, corresponding to the (002) crystal surface of graphene. All diffraction peaks of MoS2 belong to the hexagonal crystal system of the original lattice of MoS2 (JCPDS Card 37-1492), which is consistent with the literature [33]. The diffraction of MoS2/C-dots is similar to that of MoS2, indicating the decoration of C-dots without changing the MoS2 structure [34]. The slightly decreased peak intensity of (002) is attributed to the entering of C-dots into the interlayer of MoS2 
                        [35]. This indicating the introduction of C-dots did not change the crystal structure of MoS2, and the composite material was successfully synthesized. The FT-IR and BET measurements were further analyzed the functional groups and structure of samples, and the details are provided in the ESI.
